//! System call handler for MeteorOS
//!
//! This module implements the `TrapHandler` interface to handle system calls
//! from user-mode processes. It provides syscall dispatching and implementations
//! for various syscalls like read, write, open, close, etc.
//!
//! # Architecture
//!
//! The syscall handling flow:
//! 1. Hardware trap (ecall/syscall instruction) → trap handler in axhal
//! 2. axhal extracts syscall ID and arguments from registers
//! 3. axhal calls `crate::trap::handle_syscall()` (trait interface)
//! 4. TrapHandler::handle_syscall (implemented by axsyscall) dispatches to concrete syscall
//! 5. Concrete syscall implementation executes (e.g., `syscall_write`, `syscall_open`)
//! 6. Return value stored in result register (a0 on RISC-V, rax on x86_64)
//!

